1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4.
Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. e5 Nd5 8. Ne4 Qc7 9. f4 Qb6 10. c4 Bb4+ 11.
Ke2 f5 {[#]} 12. Nf2 (12. Nd6+ $2 {is simply bad, in view of} Bxd6 13. cxd5 (
13. exd6 Nf6 $17 {[%csl Ge4] Moncayo Romero-Swati, Bled 2002.}) 13... Bc5 14.
dxe6 dxe6 15. Kf3 Bd4 16. Qb3 {was played in Kholmov-Panchenko, Dnipropetrovsk
1980 and now} Qc7 $1 $17 {would have been strong, intending Rb8, c5 etc.}) (12.
exf6 {see next two chapters.}) 12... Ba6 (12... Ne7 $2 {is premature, in view
of} 13. Nd3 $1 (13. Be3 {is possible too.}) 13... Bc5 (13... d5 {is best met by
} 14. a3 $1 Bc5 15. Nxc5 Qxc5 16. Be3 {clearly favors White, as} Qxc4+ $2 {
fails to} 17. Kf2 Qe4 18. Bd3 {and the queen has been trapped.}) 14. Nxc5 Qxc5
15. b3 Qb6 16. Qd6 (16. Be3 {is also good.}) 16... c5 17. Ba3 Ng6 18. Bxc5
Nxf4+ 19. Ke3 Qxd6 20. Bxd6 Ng6 21. b4 $16 {and White is close to winning in
Navara-Vocaturo, Prague 2019.}) (12... Bc5 $2 {has regularly been played,
though after} 13. Nd3 $1 Ne3 14. Qb3 Nxf1 15. Qxb6 Bxb6 16. Rxf1 $16 {[%csl
